The most urgent and scorchingly-dangerous take of twitter is @Logo_Daedalus' call for you to steal as many old and rare books from libraries before they are destroyed, thrown in a gutter or a fire, or taken away by evil men. I dreamed about doing it with a friend last night.

Time is running away. There are expensive and hard-to-find tomes catching mold in your local library. Free them; seize them.

I volunteered in a library briefly in the past (laughably bad experience, but was shown a secret underground room). Many exquisite exemplars - untouched.
